The the quest to the truth is split into two mutually irreconciliable paths that lead either to sentimental truth or logical Truth.
-- Sentimental truth
	  -- Appeal to dogma 
	  -- Powered by hopes and expectations
	  -- Subjective in perspective
	  -- Encourages lazy thinking
	  -- Outcome never guaranteed
	  -- Closed to inquiry
	  -- Hard to challenge
	  -- Too easily abused and exploited
	  -- Knowledge of which binds people in chains and puts control in the hands of others
	  -- Loved by people in authority
	  
-- Logical Truth
	  -- Appeal to reason 
	  -- Powered by reality
	  -- Objective in perspective
	  -- Encourages inquisitiveness and curiosity
	  -- Consistently demonstrable outcomes
	  -- Open to inquiry
	  -- Can be constantly challenged
	  -- Hard to pervese once fully understood
	  -- Knowledge of which empowers
	  -- Respected by people in authority
			  
